Error handling strategy:

1. Custom exception hierarchy:
- BusinessException → 409 Conflict
- NotFoundException → 404
- ValidationException → 400
- (unexpected) → 500

2. @ControllerAdvice centralizes handling:
```java
@ControllerAdvice
public class GlobalExceptionHandler {
    @ExceptionHandler(NotFoundException.class)
    public ResponseEntity<ErrorResponse> handle(NotFoundException ex) {
        return ResponseEntity.status(404)
            .body(new ErrorResponse(ex.getMessage(), "NOT_FOUND"));
    }
}
```

3. Consistent error response DTO:
```json
{"message": "Turma not found", "code": "NOT_FOUND", "timestamp": "..."}
```

4. Never expose stack traces in production
5. Log full details server-side for debugging
6. Bean Validation errors → collect all violations → 400 with field-level errors
